metadata.name: Vibranchium
metadata.description: 𝙑𝙞𝙗𝙧𝙖𝙣𝙘𝙝𝙞𝙪𝙢: A term formed from the combination of "vibration" and "branchium" (from the Latin word "brachium," meaning "arm" or "branch"). Vibranchium refers to a structure, framework, or extension that enables the exploration and interaction with varying frequencies, energies, or dimensions.
